The paper deals with semantic segmentation, which is a computer vision task, hence it is likely to belong to the cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) sub-category. The paper also proposes a new network architecture, which involves the use of convolutional layers, making it relevant to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of residual-based boundary refinement, which is a technique used in neural networks, making it relevant to the cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) sub-category. Finally, the paper mentions the use of benchmarks to evaluate the proposed approach, which is relevant to the cs.MM (Multimedia) sub-category.
